{
  "text": "We examined (Table 1) , as a sign of viral adaptation to swine [CITATION_1] , and shared with the Papenburg strains four of five of the unique substitutions (G172E, I183V, S200P, S202N, D204S) in the antigenic site of HA [CITATION_2] . It was also possible to detect three H1N2 viruses of genotype 7 (*** Figure 5) in 2014 with endemic Italian external genes and H1N1pdm09 internal genes, all harbouring the pig adaptive hallmark, D53E mutation, in NP putative protein (Table 1 ",
